In re SLIMMAN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 4, 1903.) No. 176. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. E. Frayer, for appellant. E. Putney, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and TOWNSEND, Circuit Judges.

Appeal dismissed, the court holding that petition for review is the only remedy.
